oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Aerial view of Old Hickory community
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Large aerial photograph shows original housing in the Old Hickory community. A major road, now Old Hickory Boulevard, can be seen running top to bottom. Nashville Banner photograph by Bill Goodman. The DuPont Old Hickory Gunpowder Plant produced smokeless powder during World War I. They ceased production in 1919, but DuPont returned in 1928 and began producing Reemay, Rayon, and Cellophane.
